children.text: The perimeters of the ceiling that is to be square set has not been properly battened or trimmed for perimeter fixings at 150mm centres to prevent the ceiling from failure.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The plasterboard manufacturer in their installation instructions state that
‘Ceiling battens or furring channels are recommended for square set finish to minimise the risk of localised cracking’
, and in their ‘Fixing to Ceilings’ section that
‘It is recommended that at sheet ends screws are spaced at 300mm maximum centres for cornices and 150mm maximum centres for square set finish’

The builder should install additional battens throughout the square set areas to allow the plasterboard to be fixed at 150mm centres along the batten, in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements.
